  "prompt": "What is nerve cell?",
  "response": "A nerve cell, also known as a neuron, is the basic functional unit of the nervous system. Here are key details about nerve cells:\n\n1. Structure:\n- Cell body (soma)\n- Dendrites (receive signals)\n- Axon (transmits signals)\n- Axon terminals\n\n2. Functions:\n- Transmit electrical and chemical signals\n- Process and communicate information\n- Enable communication within the nervous system\n- Control body movements and sensory perception\n\n3. Types:\n- Sensory neurons\n- Motor neurons\n- Interneurons\n\n4. Characteristics:\n- Specialized for communication\n- Can generate and transmit electrical impulses\n- Connected to other neurons through synapses\n- Cannot typically regenerate if damaged\n\n5. Components:\n- Nucleus\n- Mitochondria\n- Cytoplasm\n- Synaptic vesicles\n\n6. Signal transmission:\n- Uses electrical and chemical signals\n- Communicates through neurotransmitters\n- Enables rapid information processing\n\nNerve cells are crucial for maintaining brain function, controlling bodily movements, processing sensory information, and supporting overall nervous system operations.",
